comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-07T17:05:16.920Z",maintainer-agent,"Audit 2026-06-07 (PR pass): CLI/agent-UX findings — SHIPPED pm-g799 (close-reason never-block), pm-ryik (--path .agents/pm discovery), pm-wrqk (dead-code+version dedup). TRACKED: pm-e7dn (runUpdate refactor), pm-vhx6 (compact trailer trim), pm-6l17 (--tags never-block alias), pm-q0kr (slim guided-error boilerplate). See ADR pm-96wm."
  "2026-06-25T00:04:16.271Z",subagent-cli-ux-20260625,"Evidence 2026-06-25 CLI/agent-UX audit: pm-mthy exists on HEAD main; current worktree has completion patch in src/cli/commands/completion.ts and tests/unit/commands/completion-command.spec.ts. Live contracts: package/packages include --declarative; extension does not. pm completion requires guide-shell here. New UX gap: pm package descirbe/catalogx --json treats typo as target and suggests --install <value> instead of did-you-mean describe/catalog."
  "2026-06-25T00:41:53.746Z",codex-audit-20260625,"Audit evidence: CLI/agent UX review fixed concrete lifecycle typo recovery issue pm-js02 so package/extension action typos like descirbe/catalogx/lis/unistall return unknown_lifecycle_action with deterministic suggested_retry instead of misleading install-target guidance."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-07T10:06:54.689Z",audit-cli-schema-agent,"Audit complete. Evidence gathered:\n1. pm search missing --updated-after/--updated-before/--created-after/--created-before/--assignee/--sprint/--release/--parent filters vs pm list (src/cli/commands/search.ts SearchOptions interface + SEARCH_FLAG_CONTRACTS). Not in MCP TOOL_SEARCH_FILTER_OPTION_CONTRACTS either.\n2. pm context has no --parent/--epic scope filter (ContextOptions interface, no parent field; register-operations.ts context registration).\n3. show-status missing from all 3 shell completions (bash line 416, zsh line 1033, fish line 1891 in completion.ts) — SCHEMA_SUBCOMMANDS has it but hand-maintained lists don't.\n4. id_prefix, author_default, output.default_format, locks.ttl_seconds NOT in pm config set (not in CONFIG_KEY_VALUES nor nested-settings.ts) — require manual settings.json edit.\n5. pm schema has no add-field/remove-field/list-fields subcommands — schema/fields.json must be hand-edited; pm schema list does not show runtime fields.\n6. schema.unknown_field_policy not settable via pm config set.\n7. pm schema apply-preset (standalone) doesn't exist — --type-preset only works on pm init, not already-initialized projects.\n8. CONFIGURATION.md has zero mention of schema/fields.json or custom field authoring.\n9. pm-haak VERDICT: FIXED. The SettingsPersistSourceSnapshot mechanism in settings.ts (resolvePersistedFileBackedSchemaSections, buildSettingsPersistSourceSnapshot, attachSettingsPersistSourceSnapshot) correctly tracks file-backed source vs merged and restores source-only values on write. close_reason confirms implementation with tests."
body: "Items created in this audit session: pm-13nx (search filter parity), pm-ds0m (context --parent scope), pm-6qi8 (completion show-status drift), pm-9byd (config set id_prefix/author_default), pm-vhbf (schema add-field), pm-nnaq (config unknown_field_policy), pm-86ob (schema apply-preset), pm-izx5 (docs fields.json). pm-haak VERDICT: FIXED."
